Package: evaluatr
Title: Secure Independent Evaluation of Clinical Prediction Models
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Joie", "Ensor", email = "j.ensor@bham.ac.uk", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Provides a two-component system for independent evaluation of clinical
    prediction models while preserving commercial viability and data sovereignty.
    Evaluators can retrieve model specifications from a developer's private GitHub
    repository (using a time-limited fine-grained personal access token) and compute
    predictions locally on their own dataset, without ever exposing the model
    coefficients or transmitting patient data. Performance metrics and diagnostic
    plots for binary prediction models are included.
